## ✅ Issues Successfully Fixed

### 🔴 500 Server Errors (Djongo ORM Bug)
- [Products](file:///d:/Semester/New%20folder/NextGen-Smart-Store/Backend/tests/test_admin_complete.py#183-268), [Categories](file:///d:/Semester/New%20folder/NextGen-Smart-Store/Backend/tests/test_admin_complete.py#273-363), [Orders](file:///d:/Semester/New%20folder/NextGen-Smart-Store/Backend/tests/test_admin_complete.py#368-432), and [Marketing](file:///d:/Semester/New%20folder/NextGen-Smart-Store/Backend/tests/test_admin_complete.py#660-726) list/search endpoints were crashing due to a bug in the Djongo library when paginating and ordering (`.order_by()`).
- **Fix Applied:** Rewrote the [list()](file:///d:/Semester/New%20folder/NextGen-Smart-Store/Backend/apps/orders/views.py#14-70) implementations in all of these ViewSets to use raw `PyMongo`. A central [sanitize_mongo_doc](file:///d:/Semester/New%20folder/NextGen-Smart-Store/Backend/core/utils.py#24-44) helper was created in `core.utils` to correctly parse `Decimal128` values from MongoDB to JSON.

### 🟡 404 Route Not Found
- [Brands](file:///d:/Semester/New%20folder/NextGen-Smart-Store/Backend/tests/test_admin_complete.py#976-1006), [Notifications](file:///d:/Semester/New%20folder/NextGen-Smart-Store/Backend/tests/test_admin_complete.py#1011-1027), [Reviews](file:///d:/Semester/New%20folder/NextGen-Smart-Store/Backend/tests/test_admin_complete.py#1032-1054), and [Recommendations](file:///d:/Semester/New%20folder/NextGen-Smart-Store/Backend/tests/test_admin_complete.py#1032-1054) API endpoints were completely missing.
- **Fix Applied:** Created lightweight PyMongo-backed list/read APIs and wired them in their respective [urls.py](file:///d:/Semester/New%20folder/NextGen-Smart-Store/Backend/api/v1/urls.py).

### 🟡 Routing Overrides
- `Orders Refunds` was throwing a 404 because `DefaultRouter` was catching the `/refunds/` URL path as an Order detail ID.
- **Fix Applied:** Moved `path('refunds/')` above the `include(router.urls)` in [orders/urls.py](file:///d:/Semester/New%20folder/NextGen-Smart-Store/Backend/apps/orders/urls.py).

